01-02 September - Old Fashioned Brownies

- 1   cup sugar
- 1/3 cup softened butter
- 2/3 cup flour
- 1/4 teaspoon salt
- 2   oz Nestle's choco-bake  (editor's note: this doesn't exist anymore, but you can use 6 tablespoons cocoa powder and 2 tablespoon shortening instead)
- 2   eggs
- 1   teaspoon vanilla
- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder
- 1/2 cup chopped nuts

In a bowl combine sugar, eggs, butter, chocolate, and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Add flour, baking powder, salt mix well. Add nuts. Spread in greased 8" square pan. Bake in a preheated 350F oven for about 25-30 minutes. Cool, then cut into 2" squares. 